<h4 style="text-align: center;">Other</h4>
<div id="testAccordion" style="min-height: auto; width: 100%;" align="left">
<h3><a href="#resourcesSharedapicMembers">Resources shared by APIC members</a></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<ul>
<li><a style="font-size: 1em; font-weight: normal;" href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/PPE_Buddy_System_Process_10.27.14_at_MHfS.pdf">Buddy system for PPE placement and removal</a><span style="font-size: 1em; font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;(Methodist Hospital for Surgery)</span></li>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/Donning_and_Doffing_PPE_COMPETENCY_VALIDATION_CHECKLIST.pdf" target="_blank">Donning and doffing PPE competency validation checklist</a> (American Association for Respiratory Care)</li>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/Donning_and_Doffing_PPE_Competency_10282014_doc.pdf" target="_blank">Donning and doffing PPE for isolation of Ebola patients</a>&nbsp;(Pipestone County Medical Center and Family Clinic Avera)</li>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/MDI_Donning_10.28.pdf" target="_blank">PPE donning checklist</a> (Mount Desert Island Hospital)</li>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/MDI_Doffing_10.28.pdf" target="_blank">PPE doffing checklist</a>&nbsp;(Mount Desert Island Hospital)</li>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/Ebola_Teaching_Points.pdf" target="_blank">Teaching points for nurse educators</a>&nbsp;(The Ohio State University)</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h3><a href="#personalProtectiveEquipment">Personal protective equipment</a></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/procedures-for-ppe.html" target="_blank">Guidance on Personal Protective Equipment To Be Used by Healthcare Workers During Management of Patients with Ebola Virus Disease in U.S. Hospitals, Including Procedures for Putting On (Donning) and Removing (Doffing)</a>&mdash;Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</li>
<li>Interactive,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/ppe-training/index.html">web-based training on PPE</a>, developed by APIC, Johns Hopkins Armstrong Intitute for Patient Safety and Quality, and CDC</li>
<li><a href="http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/put_on_ppequipment.pdf?ua=1" target="_blank">Steps to put on personal protective equipment (PPE)</a>&mdash;World Health Organization</li>
<li><a href="http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/remove_ppequipment.pdf?ua=1" target="_blank">Steps to remove personal protective equipment (PPE)</a> &mdash;World Health Organization</li>
<li>Videos:&nbsp;</li>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N6F61J93FvE" target="_blank">Donning and Doffing of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) in Hospital Ebola Isolation Units</a>&mdash;North Carolina Preferred Guidance&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AxdlOqs2_ww" target="_blank">Ebola Education Session - Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) Demonstration</a>&mdash;GNYHA/1199SEIU</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</div>
<h3><a href="#resourcesOutsideOrganizations">Resources from additional outside organizations</a></h3>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.allhealth.org/publications/Public_health/Ebola-Toolkit_161.pdf" target="_blank">Alliance for Health Reform</a>&mdash;Toolkit: Emergency Preparedness in the U.S.: The Ebola Threat</li>
<li><a href="http://www.absa.org/resebola.html" target="_blank">American Biological Safety Association</a>&mdash;Ebola webpage</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ama-assn.org/ama/pub/physician-resources/public-health/ebola-resource-center.page" target="_blank">American Medical Association</a>&mdash;Ebola resource center</li>
<li><a href="http://www.getreadyforflu.org/EbolaFacts.htm" target="_blank">American Public Health Association</a>&mdash;Ebola: What you need to know if you live in the U.S.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.aami.org/publications/AAMINews/Nov2014/ebola_outbreak.html" target="_blank">Association for the Advancement of Medical Instrumentation</a>&mdash;Healthcare Organizations Respond to Ebola Outbreak</li>
<li><a href="http://www.aorn.org/Clinical_Practice/Clinical_FAQs/Ebola.aspx" target="_blank">Association of periOperative Registered Nurses</a>&mdash;Clinical FAQ</li>
<li><a href="http://www.astho.org/Infectious-Disease/Top-Questions-On-Ebola-Simple-Answers-Developed-by-ASTHO/" target="_blank">Association of State and Territorial Health Officials</a>&mdash;Top Questions On Ebola: Simple Answers&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/" target="_blank">Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</a>&mdash;</li>
<ul>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/Key_Messages_11-19__FINAL.pdf" target="_blank">Ebola-related key messages and talking points</a>, November 19</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/procedures-for-ppe.html" target="_self">Guidance on Personal Protective Equipment to be used by healthcare workers during management of patients with Ebola virus disease in U.S. hospitals, including procedures for putting on (donning) and removing (doffing)</a></li>
</ul>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/CMS_Ebola_state_memo.pdf" target="_blank">Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services</a>&mdash;Emergency Medical Treatment and Labor Act (EMTALA) requirements and implications related to Ebola virus disease (Ebola) memo</li>
<li><a href="/Resource_/TinyMceFileManager/Topic-specific/suspected_ebola_patient_packaging_guidance_final.pdf" target="_blank">Department of Transportation</a>&mdash;Procedural Guidance on the Proper Packaging of Ebola Suspected Waste</li>
<li><a href="http://www.emoryhealthcare.org/ebola-protocol/pdf/ehc-evd-protocols.pdf" target="_blank">Emory Healthcare</a>&mdash;Ebola Preparedness Protocols</li>
<li><a href="http://vimeo.com/109626204" target="_blank">Greater New York Hospital Association/1199SEIU Healthcare Education&nbsp;Project</a>&mdash;Personal protective equipment (PPE) training demonstration. October 21, 2014,&nbsp;ARCHIVED</li>
<li><a href="http://www.idsociety.org/Index.aspx" target="_blank">Infectious Diseases Society of America</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/833907" target="_blank">Medscape</a>&mdash;Ebola: Donning and doffing of personal protective equipment (PPE)</li>
<li><a href="https://www.unmc.edu/cce/neb_ebola.htm" target="_blank">The Nebraska Ebola method for clinicians</a>&nbsp;(The University of Nebraska Medical Center and Nebraska Medicine)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nln.org/facultyprograms/ebolaresources.htm" target="_blank">National League for Nursing</a>&mdash;Dealing with Ebola and other dire infectious diseases</li>
<li><a href="http://disasterinfo.nlm.nih.gov/dimrc/ebola_2014.html" target="_blank">National Library of Medicine</a>&mdash;Disaster medicine and public health information resources</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N6F61J93FvE" target="_blank">North Carolina Preferred Guidance</a>&mdash;Donning and Doffing of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) in Hospital Ebola Isolation Units</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nslijalerts.com/homepage/ebola-virus/for-healthcare-organizations/north-shore-lij-ebola-virus-preparedness-manual/?utm_source=pr&amp;utm_medium=bitly&amp;utm_campaign=ebola-pr-bitly" target="_blank">North Shore-LIJ Health System</a>&mdash;Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) Preparedness Manual</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dol.gov/osha/pdf/OSHA_FS-3761_PPE_Selection_Matrix_-_Ebola_(11-24-14).pdf" target="_blank">Occupational Safety and Health Administration</a>&mdash;PPE Selection Matrix for Occupational Exposure to Ebola Virus:&nbsp;Guidance for common exposure scenarios</li>
<li><a href="http://www.shea-online.org/View/ArticleId/301/Ebola-Infection-Control-Resources.aspx" target="_blank">Society for Healthcare Epidemiology of America</a>&mdash;Ebola Infection Control Resources</li>
<li><a href="http://www.jointcommission.org/topics/ebola_preparedness_resources.aspx" target="_blank">The Joint Commission</a>&mdash;Ebola preparedness resources
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.jointcommission.org/assets/1/18/Joint_Commission_Standards_for_Managing_Ebola_Patient.pdf" target="_blank">Joint Commission Standards: Safely and Effectively Managing the Infectious Ebola Patient</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.jointcommission.org/important_ebola_information_for_laboratorians/" target="_blank">Ebola information for laboratories</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/en/" target="_blank">World Health Organization</a>&mdash;Ebola Virus Disease</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>APIC is working with the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/" target="_blank">Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</a>&nbsp;(CDC), the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/en/" target="_blank">World Health Organization</a>&nbsp;(WHO), and other domestic and international partners in response to the current outbreak by helping and coordinating needed expertise with the relevant government agencies and keeping our members updated on what they need to know to be effective in the U.S.</p>
<p>APIC members served as faculty for the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/safety-training-course/index.html?s_cid=cs_1344" target="_blank">CDC training course</a>&nbsp;that prepare U.S. healthcare workers before deploying to West Africa.</p>
<p>Infection preventionists who are interested in working directly with the Ebola response teams in West Africa need to work through the relevant agencies, including&nbsp;<a href="http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/en/" target="_blank">WHO</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.doctorswithoutborders.org/our-work/medical-issues/ebola" target="_blank">Doctors Without Borders</a>, and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/safety-training-course/index.html?s_cid=cs_1344" target="_blank">CDC</a>. CDC directs people to&nbsp;<a href="http://www.usaid.gov/ebola/volunteers" target="_blank">USAID</a>.</p>
<p>APIC will continuously notify members of updated&nbsp;Ebola-related resources&nbsp;from APIC, CDC, and other organizations.&nbsp;</p></div>  
                    
                </div>
            </div>
